{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775865677697,"sessionID":"ses_28628d211ffeepx3580r55PAKi","part":{"id":"prt_d79d7c1a4001uByDeTlVahK53U","messageID":"msg_d79d7b2610015Jg3MkaHg5a6BJ","sessionID":"ses_28628d211ffeepx3580r55PAKi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_90d719ee8020430da2f9337f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the DockerService encapsulation in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-024\n10: - **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: DockerService is a core service class that encapsulates all Docker operations needed by the AgentCube CLI. It provides a clean abstraction layer over the Docker SDK, enabling the CLI to build, push, and manage container images without directly coupling to docker-py implementation details. The service handles Docker availability checks, image building with build args, image info retrieval, image pushing to registries with authentication, and image removal.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-024-001: Docker availability check\n25: \n26: The system SHALL verify Docker daemon is accessible before performing any Docker operations.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-024-001-A — Docker running returns true\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is running and accessible via `docker.from_env()`\n31: - **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called\n32: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: AR-024-001-B — Docker not running returns false\n35: \n36: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running or not accessible\n37: - **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called and `docker.from_env()` raises `docker.errors.DockerException` or `docker.errors.APIError`\n38: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `False` and log a warning message\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: AR-024-001-C — Docker not installed returns false\n41: \n42: - **GIVEN** Docker is not installed or the Docker socket is unavailable\n43: - **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called and a `ConnectionError` or `FileNotFoundError` occurs\n44: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `False`\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ### AR-024-002: Image building\n49: \n50: The system SHALL build container images from Dockerfiles using the Docker SDK.\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 370. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the DockerService encapsulation in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-024\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nDockerService is a core service class that encapsulates all Docker operations needed by the AgentCube CLI. It provides a clean abstraction layer over the Docker SDK, enabling the CLI to build, push, and manage container images without directly coupling to docker-py implementation details. The service handles Docker availability checks, image building with build args, image info retrieval, image pushing to registries with authentication, and image removal.\n\n---","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775865677672,"end":1775865677694}}}}
